   <category name='gifts'>

      <section name='card'>

         <para number='1' comment='loc 198 - Get trading card'>
         You reach for one of the cards, but quick as a flash, Clive picks up a wooden ruler from under the counter and whacks your hand with it. "No touching," he says in a nasal whine. "These collectibles are very valuable, so keep your grubby hands off them."
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Buy trading card'>
         There are a multitude of cards to choose from, so you need to specify which one you want to buy.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Get current card'>
         Clive yelps in alarm as you try to pick up the special card. He grabs it off the counter before you can touch it. "No handling the merchandise," he squeaks, and points to the sign on the wall. "You pay for it, then you fondle it - until then, hands off."
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='Buy current card - already got'>
         Clive scowls at you. "These are limited edition trading cards, get it? One per customer, that's all. You can't fool me - I know you already bought one of those. I have a good memory."
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='Sell player a card'>
         Clive carefully - almost reverently - takes one of the Catty trading cards and places it in a special display holder. He hands it to you and you clip it to your belt.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='No slithy'>
         Clive scowls at you. "These are very valuable trading cards, and they cost one slithy tove. I can see you haven't got a slithy so don't you try to rip me off. You get yourself a slithy then you can come back - until then, get out of my shop."
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='expired'>

         <para number='1' comment='Player tries to buy old card'>
         Clive looks as if he regrets the chance to take a slithy off you, as he says, "That trading card was a special limited edition offer, and it's run out now. But you could buy the current card in the collection." He points to the display on the counter.
         </para>

